FBIS3-35462 "drnes038_p_94005" FBIS-NES-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Feb 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Dostam's Forces Attack Kondoz; Extensive Losses Noted LD2402201594 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 GMT 24 Feb 94 LD2402201594 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Language: Pashto Article Type:BFN [Text] The infamous militia of the fiendish triangle today mounted a failed attack in Kondoz in which they, at the blessing of God and the battle of the Islamic Army, suffered a heavy defeat and extensive losses. The infamous militia, who attacked the area of Qotailich and kidnapped several people, faced the fatal blows of the ambush units of Corp No. 6, Brigade 54, and mechanized forces. The Islamic Army of Afghanistan entered the region and inflicted heavy losses on the militia. As a result of the blows, three pieces of mortar, three pieces of 82-mm artillery, 80 Kalashnikovs, 10 pieces of RPG8 and [words indistinct] desert artillery, and a ZK1 machinegun of the enemy have been captured by the Islamic Army of Afghanistan. [Word indistinct] of the invaders were captured, and 15 others, including two generals by the names of Gholam Rasul and (?Mohammad) Saleh, were killed. As a result of the counteroffensive and the heroism and bravery of the Islamic Army of Afghanistan, the areas of [words indistinct] were cleared of the militia.
